n multiple honeypot daemons on the same network interface while maintaining a small footprint and constrain each honeypot within its own environment. Installation over vanilla Ubuntu - <a href=\"https://github.com/dtag-dev-sec/t-pot-autoinstall\">T-Pot Autoinstall</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/dtag-dev-sec/t-pot-autoinstall\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">128</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":128,\"repo\":\"dtag-dev-sec/t-pot-autoinstall\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - This script will install T-Pot 16.04/17.10 on a fresh Ubuntu 16.04.x LTS (64bit). It is intended to be used on hosted servers, where an Ubuntu base image is given and there is no ability to install custom ISO images. Successfully tested on vanilla Ubuntu 16.04.3 in VMware.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-29T14:26:01.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"qazbnm456/awesome-web-security","categoryHTML":"<h2>Miscellaneous</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://voidsec.com/vpn-leak/\">TL:DR: VPN leaks users’ IPs via WebRTC. I’ve tested seventy VPN providers and 16 of them leaks users’ IPs via WebRTC (23%)</a> - Written by <a href=\"https://voidsec.com/\">voidsec</a>.</li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-29T13:15:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"NARKOZ/guides","categoryHTML":"<h2>Programming Languages</h2><h3>JavaScript</h3>","itemHTML":"<li>[UPDATED] <a href=\"https://google.github.io/styleguide/jsguide.html\">Google JavaScript Style Guide</a></li>","updatedAt":"2018-03-29T08:25:05.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"e